import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    x_ticks = plt.xticks()[0]
    if len(x_ticks) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['open'], label='Open')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'], label='Close')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.boxplot(data['ret'])
    plt.title("What is the distribution of return percentages?")
    plt.xlabel("Return Percentage")
    plt.ylabel("Value")
    plt.xticks([1], ['ret'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
